 distributions obtained\nfrom two models: a population synthesis model, and a model where planetary\nsystems are constructed by randomly picking synthetic planets. The observed\ndistribution is shown to be closer to the one derived from the population\nsynthesis model than from the random systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Jan 2019 14:57:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-10"}
